vior of African Commodity/Product Markets and Market Institutions and Their Consequences for Economic Growth. CID Working Paper no. 35, January 2000.   </p>\r\n<p>Voortman, R.L., B.G.J.S. Sonneveld, and M.A. Keyzer. African Land Ecology: Opportunities and Constraints for Agricultural Development. CID Working Paper no. 37, January 2000. </p>";s:6:"teaser";s:294:"<p><em>The Africa Research Program at Harvard University focuses on the development of political institutions, the determinants of investment and growth, and the relationship between economics, politics and violence.</em> <a href="http://africa.gov.harvard.edu">(Website on Africa data)</a></p>";s:3:"log";s:0:"";s:6:"format";s:1:"1";s:3:"uid";s:2:"14";s:4:"name";s:6:"rbates";s:7:"picture";s:0:"";s:4:"data";s:24:"a:1:{s:7:"contact";i:1;}";s:4:"path";s:30:"rbates/africa-research-program";s:9:"og_groups";a:1:{i:0;i:227;}s:14:"og_groups_both";a:1:{i:227;s:6:"rbates";}s:9:"og_public";b:1;s:4:"tags";a:1:{i:6;a:1:{i:105;O:8:"stdClass":5:{s:3:"tid";s:3:"105";s:3:"vid";s:1:"6";s:4:"name";s:15:"africa research";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:6:"weight";s:1:"0";}}}s:22:"last_comment_timestamp";s:10:"1224709810";s:17:"last_comment_name";N;s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:8:"taxonomy";a:1:{i:105;r:29;}s:5:"files";a:1:{i:95;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:3:"fid";s:2:"95";s:3:"nid";s:3:"238";s:8:"filename";s:24:"African_Leaders_2004.xls";s:8:"filepath";s:49:"files/scholar/uploads/14/African_Leaders_2004.xls";s:8:"filemime";s:24:"application/vnd.ms-excel";s:8:"filesize";s:5:"49664";s:3:"vid";s:3:"238";s:11:"description";s:24:"African_Leaders_2004.xls";s:4:"list";s:1:"1";}}}'),
